1. When you are working with multiple people on a project and you all need to be able to collaborate effectively. 
2. When you are working with other people you would not necessarily want all of their changes to be automatically sent to your local version of the project. 
3. Forking is for cloning within GitHub, cloning is for making a copy of a repository from one place to another, and branches are for when you want to develop something on the side of the master branch of your application. 